entity.name: Cal Naughton Jr.
entity.text:
Cal Naughton Jr. is an American former racing driver. Naughton is best known for driving the Old Spice no. 47 Chevrolet for Dennit Racing, where he won the 2005 NASCAR Nextel Cup Series.

Cal Naughton, Jr.

Image 4: Cal Naughton Jr

### Relatives [...] Naughton Jr started his NASCAR career as a pit crew member for Dennit Racing. When Dennit Racing expanded to two cars, Naughton drove the no. 47 with primary sponsorship from Old Spice.

### Ricky Bobby's no. 2[]

For many years, Cal was Ricky Bobby's wingman. Often employing what they called "Shake and Bake". Prior to the ending of the 2003 Daytona 500, Naughton and Bobby used this to slingshot past Michael Waltrip.

### 2005: Championship season[]
